name: PLH - Survey - Parenting & Behaviour - Questions & Comparison

actions.text:
It is hard to find time to have fun with your children. How many days in the past week did you do something fun together? (0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7)

If you don't want to answer, please type 99.

Sorry, I don't understand what you mean. Please reply with a number between 0 and 7.
If you don't want to answer, please type 99.
Well done for spending time with your child, it makes all the difference!
Amazing that you keep doing fun things with your child. You are the best parent they could wish for!
So good that you and your child are having fun times together. Your hard work is paying off, you can be proud of yourself!
Well done for spending time to do something fun with your child! You are making great progress. Keep it up!
Great that you are setting aside time with your child – it is THE foundation for a happy home!
I know it is hard to find time in our busy lives. Well done for trying your best!
Finding time to do something fun with your child can be hard, I understand! The great thing is that spending time together will make other things go easier – you will see!
Give yourself credit for trying. Even 5 minutes a day can make a BIG difference!
I understand that it can be difficult to find time to spend with your child. Well done for trying, you can do it!
Life can get so busy sometimes, I know! If you start spending time together doing one small activity, it will get easier over time!

Focusing on the positive will help you see that behaviour more. How many days in the past week have you praised your child? (0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7)

If you don't want to answer, please type 99.

Sorry, I don't understand what you mean. Please reply with a number between 0 and 7.
If you don't want to answer, please type 99.
Wonderful that you are praising your child! This helps them feel seen and loved – your encouragement means a lot.
I understand it can be hard to praise your child sometimes. Remember, your praise makes a big difference, even if you don’t see it right away!
It is great that you are praising your child for things they do well. As you appreciate them, they will also start appreciating you and the others in your family more – you set the best example!

We all sometimes feel like our children are causing more negativity than positivity. Try to see through negative attitudes and praise any positive behaviour you notice. With time, you will see the change!
Sorry that it has been harder for you to praise your child. Try to find something positive, even if it is small. Over time, they will appreciate that you notice when they do something well.

With everything that is going on, it is not always easy to focus on the positive. Try to find 10 minutes to pay attention to what your child is doing – perhaps you can praise them for helping with a chore or for doing their homework? It helps a lot!
So good to hear you are telling your child when they are doing something well. With time, you will see them do that behaviour more and more. You are doing a great job!
Sometime our children don’t seem to do or say many things that deserve praise. Start praising the small things, you will see your child showing more positive behaviour over time!
Well done for praising your child. Praise will help your child feel good about themselves, and they will show even more positive behaviour!

This is a very stressful time for families. How many days in the past week did you feel very stressed as a parent/caregiver? (0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7)

If you don't want to answer, please type 99.
Great work! By praising your child, yourself and your other family members, you are making your house a happy home!

Sorry, I don't understand what you mean. Please reply with a number between 0 and 7.
If you don't want to answer, please type 99.
Did you know that you are less stressed than you were last week? Amazing!
It’s wonderful to hear you are feeling less stress than last week. Keep up the good work!
Amazing that you are feeling less stressed! Remember to keep taking a deep breath every time something makes you feel anxious – you are doing a great job!
We understand that this is a stressful time. Remember that you are not alone. We are here to help!
Life can be overwhelming sometimes. Well done for trying your best, you are valued and appreciated!
We all feel stressed sometimes, it’s normal. Remember to be kind to yourself and take a minute for yourself when you need it, you are doing a great job!
It is great you are feeling less stressed. We all have our ups and downs – remember the good times whenever things get challenging!
Well done for managing your stress! Life can get overwhelming sometimes, but remember you can always take a pause – you are doing amazing.
It can be stressful to get through the day sometimes. At the end of each day, remember to praise yourself for doing your best!
It is okay to feel overwhelmed from time to time, we all do! Take a deep breath and remember that we are here to help.
Would you like a brief activity to help you with stress?
Sorry, I don't understand what you mean.
Sit down, close your eyes and listen to your breath as it goes in and out. Notice how you feel. When you are ready open your eyes again. Everything is okay.
Here's a quick video to help you take a pause!
Here's an audio message to help you take a pause!
We hope that was helpful! Remember you can always type "Help" at anytime if you need an activity to help you relax or reduce stress.

It is so stressful when children misbehave. How many days in the past week did you physically discipline your children by hitting, spanking, or slapping with your hand or an object like a stick or a belt? (0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7)

If you don't want to answer, please type 99.

Sorry, I don't understand what you mean. Please reply with a number between 0 and 7.
If you don't want to answer, please type 99.
Great to see you are managing to respond calmly to your child, that’s a big accomplishment! Celebrate this win, you are a star.

It sounds like you are having have a difficult time with your child. This can be really hard so be patient with yourself. Try to take a pause (even one deep breath!) next time and respond differently. You can do it!
It can be so difficult to keep calm when things get out of hand. Try again next time – each day is a new opportunity!
Well done! Learning new ways of responding to your children when they misbehave will make a BIG difference in the way they learn how to resolve conflicts as they get older.
Amazing! You are setting such a great example for your children on how to respond calmly in difficult situations – keep up the good work!
So good! Every time you choose to respond calm but clear, you are showing your child how much you care about them. They will feel heard and loved, and will be more likely to listen to you!
Sometimes everything gets too much! Remember to recognise when you feel that way and take a few deep breaths before responding. Your child will learn from your good example!
Well done for managing your emotions! When things get tough, you can always take a pause and address the problem later on when everyone is calm. You are doing a great job.
It is wonderful that you are responding in a calm way when your child does something upsetting. They can learn so much from you!
Our children sometimes drive us crazy. Remember, you can always take a pause and address the problem later on when everyone is calm. You can do it!
Sorry that things are not always easy with your child. When they upset you, try to remain calm, That way, you can keep clear boundaries and solve problems together. You can do it!
We all struggle to stay calm sometimes. Take a deep breath and remember that mistakes are human. Talking to your child will help more in the end – you are an awesome parent!

Sometimes our children make us really upset. How many days in the past week did you shout, scream, or yell at your children? (0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7)

If you don't want to answer, please type 99.

Sorry, I don't understand what you mean. Please reply with a number between 0 and 7.
If you don't want to answer, please type 99.
Being a parent is not easy. Try to be patient with yourself and your family, and take some space if you need it. By talking about our challenges calmly, we can solve them together!
Sorry that you are having a difficult time with your child. It happens to all of us. Remember, every day we can make a new choice
It can be difficult to control our anger, especially when they make us really angry. Take a deep breath, and be proud of yourself when you manage to do it!
Well done! Brain science shows if you control your anger when your child misbehaves, you increase your child's brain development. Be proud of yourself when you manage to do it!
Well done for keeping calm in difficult situations – that is definitely not easy to do! You are setting a great example for your child.
Great work! When we respond calmly, our teens are more likely to do the same.
We all get overwhelmed sometimes. Next time when you feel angry, try taking a deep breath before responding. This helps a lot!
Our children can really drive us crazy sometimes. By responding calmly, they will learn to do the same when something upsets them at home or outside. Your patience will pay off, you will see!

When we get angry, it can be hard to stay calm. Try to recognise your emotions and those of your child, and talk about them later - this helps everyone to understand each other better next time. You can do it!
So good that you speak to your child calmly, even when they drive you crazy. You can be proud of yourself! Remember to keep taking deep breaths every time you feel they are testing your patience.
It is great that you can address your child more and more calmly when they upset you. Working through challenges together will help your child so much in life – you are doing amazing!
Wonderful to hear that you are managing to stay calm in difficult situations. You can be proud of yourself – keep up the great work!

It can sometimes be difficult to have a positive relationship with our children. How confident do you feel about your ability as a parent/caregiver to have a positive relationship with your children? (0=not confident to 7=extremely confident)

If you don't want to answer, please type 99.

Sorry, I don't understand what you mean. Please reply with a number between 0 and 7.
If you don't want to answer, please type 99.

Having a positive relationship with our children can be difficult, especially during stressful times. You might want to try spending a little more One-on-One Time with your child. It will show them that they are valued and loved.
It is so wonderful to hear that you are able to maintain a positive relationship with your children. They really benefit from having you as a source of love and support in their lives.

We all want to keep our children safe. How confident do you feel you are to protect your child from sexual abuse online or in-person? (0=not confident to 7=extremely confident)

If you don't want to answer, please type 99.

Sorry, I don't understand what you mean. Please reply with a number between 0 and 7.
If you don't want to answer, please type 99.
Being a parent is not easy and comes with lots of stress and responsibilities. Well done for taking the time to learn how to keep your child safe!
Being a parent is not easy and comes with lots of stress and responsibilities. It can be difficult to know how to keep our children safe. We are here to support you!
Sometimes it can be hard to know what to do to help keep our children safe. Talk to them and get advice from people you can trust, it really helps!
Well done for learning more about how you can keep your child safe. It is not easy, but you are doing a great job – you can be proud of yourself!

So good to hear you are feeling more confident to keep your child safe! Remember, building a positive relationship with your child makes it easier to talk about difficult things, including potential risks. You are doing really well!

It is hard to know how to keep our children safe, especially if they spend time online or outside the house. By spending time with our children, they will feel free to share with us if they have questions or problems.
Well done for learning more about potential risks and how to protect your child. Knowledge is power – thank you for sharing that power with your child even it makes you feel uncomfortable sometimes!

Talking about difficult things, including the risks of sexual abuse, can be really hard. Well done for making the effort to talk about these difficult topics and questions – it really helps to keep your child safe!
You are not alone! We are all trying to figure out how to best keep our children safe, and nobody has all the answers. We are here to help!

Great that you are learning more about how to keep your child safe. Nobody has all the answers, but it makes a big difference if you and your child can talk about difficult things together. Keep up the good work!

Keeping our children safe is not easy, but by working together we can prevent and prepare for so many things! Ask your children what risks they know of, and fill in any gaps together. You make an amazing team!

Sometimes we can feel overwhelmed by the potential dangers around us. Talk to your children and people you can trust. Together we can come up with a plan to keep everyone safe – well done for putting in the work!
